A community in Chibok Local Government Area of Borno State, Korongilum has come under heavy attack by the Boko Haram sect. Many houses were set on fire by the dreaded terrorist group on Tuesday. It was gathered that residents have been running helter skelter amid shootings by the terrorists. Troops from the Nigerian Army’s 28 task force brigade and 117 battalion, both in Chibok, have moved over to the scene. Details later…